tldr: The sleep questionnaire app received a major aesthetic overhaul,
  transforming its generic look into a calming, professional, and cohesive
  sleep-themed design. This involved updating the color palette, redesigning key
  components, and applying consistent styling across all sections, along with
  fixing a console error related to input values.
overview: The user wanted to elevate the aesthetic appeal of their sleep
  questionnaire application, which initially had a generic, template-like
  appearance. The approach involved a multi-phase redesign, starting with a new
  sleep-themed color palette and custom utility classes. Key components like the
  main form layout, progress bar, and intro section were significantly enhanced
  with decorative elements, improved visual hierarchy, and interactive states.
  All 14 questionnaire sections were then systematically updated to ensure
  consistent theming, replacing old gray boxes with refined card-style groupings
  and themed text/icon colors. During the process, a console error related to
   values being passed to input elements was identified and fixed by
  ensuring  was converted to an empty string in the  component.
  Finally, further aesthetic refinements were made by introducing themed alert
  classes and increasing the opacity of section borders for better definition.
  The outcome is a visually cohesive, calming, and professional application
  tailored for sleep health assessment.
